Lee May conducts his first ``burn'' in Fightingtown Creek.
The mission: get rid of as much of the myriad of suckering sourwood stumps, briar thickets and scraggly pines as possible.
The mountain folks know ``it makes a lot more sense to burn this stuff in place than to try hauling it away.''
So, he lit up a pile and after it was safely burned out, he lit the next.
Until all piles were gone.
``My first burn.''
(May, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTO.
