DALTON,Ga.
Sam Pullen of Dalton knows roses.
He knows them so well in fact that he's still able to gather several dozens a day even though it's December.
What's his secret?
``The more you pick them, the more they bloom,'' Sam says, ``It takes a lot out of the rose bush if you don't cut them often.''
During peak season in June, Sam has picked as many as 30 dozen in one day from his 750 hybrid tea and floribunda bushes.
(Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)WITH PHOTOS.
